Package sexpression.lexer

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ILexer
    This defines the public interface of a lexer.
    ILexerState
    State Design Pattern

    Each state instance must define the following, state-dependent behavior.
    ITokenVisitor<E>
    Visitor Design Pattern

    Instances of this interface can visit a Token.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Close
    This class represents the special token "close parenthesis."
    Colon
    This class represents the special token "colon."
    CommentState  
    EOF
    This class represents the special token "EOF." Receiving an EOF token from the stream means that the given character stream has reached its end.
    Hash  
    Lexer
    This class takes any input stream and scans for the following tokens:
    colon (':')
    open paren ('(')
    close paren (')')
    words dileneated by either whitespace or one of the above tokens.
    Mod  
    Open
    This class represents the special token "open parenthesis."
    Token
    Values emitted by the lexer are all of this type.
    WhitespaceState
    State Design Pattern

    When the lexer is in this state, is in the middle of reading whitespace (not in the middle of reading a word).
    Word  
    WordState
    State Design Pattern

    When the lexer is in this state, is in the middle of reading a word.
